

Q1. stream and concurrent stream which is faster./

✅ Normal Stream

list.stream().forEach(x -> process(x));

Runs sequentially (single thread)
Order is maintained
Less overhead


✅ Parallel Stream (Concurrent Stream)

list.parallelStream().forEach(x -> process(x));

Runs using multiple threads (ForkJoinPool)
Uses all CPU cores
Order may not be maintained


4. Real Interview Answer (Best)

👉 Answer like this:

Parallel stream is not always faster than a normal stream.
It improves performance only for large datasets and CPU-intensive operations by utilizing multiple cores.
However, for small data or simple tasks, sequential streams are faster due to lower overhead.





